textBeforeTable: Date: Oct 19, 2013 • Site: Albany, N.Y.  • Stadium: Bob Ford Field  •  Attendance: 8500   TOWSON (7-1,3-1) vs. Albany (1-7,0-4) #7 TOWSON vs Albany (Oct 19, 2013 at Albany, N.Y.)   With a bye next Saturday, the Great Danes will have two weeks to prepare for CAA-foe Richmond. UAlbany will make its third trip this season to the state of Virginia on Nov. 2nd. For Towson, West finished with 183 yards and two touchdowns on the ground, carrying the ball 22 times. Athens completed 22-of-32 passes for 294 yards, a touchdown and two interceptions. Wilkins totaled 129 yards and a score on six catches.  In the fourth quarter, the Great Danes held the Tigers off the board until the final minute of play. Towson worked its way 54 yards down the gridiron on eight plays, and Trea Jones completed the drive with a 2-yard run for a touchdown with 54 seconds on the clock. With rain falling from the sky as the game neared an end, the extra point was kicked wide left, making the final score 44-17. Chillis looked to spark a comeback, returning the ball 39 yards to start UAlbany at midfield on the next drive; the senior finished with 123 all-purpose yards on the night, including 101 on five kickoff returns.
